theorem Topology.P1_closure_iff_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure (A : Set X)) ↔ Topology.P1 (X := X) A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1cl
    dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1cl ⊢
    intro x hxA
    -- `x` lies in `closure A`, so we can use `hP1cl`.
    have hx₁ : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
      have hx_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hxA
      exact hP1cl hx_closure
    -- Relate the two closures via monotonicity.
    have h_subset :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      -- First, `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
      have h_in :
          interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
        Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure_interior
          (X := X) (A := A)
      -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
      exact closure_mono h_in
    exact h_subset hx₁
  · intro hP1A
    exact Topology.P1_implies_P1_closure (X := X) (A := A) hP1A
